<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Proposed new topic: The level element.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Min">Min</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:24 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Proposed new topic: The level element.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>TheBlack and Darkblight pointed out a huge problem concerning levels making too much difference in PvP. I agree with them for it's ridiculous that a LV18 can almost always kill a LV16, this totally ruined the PK environment because it places character experience too much ahead of player skills.

<BR>The problem though is that this isn't really a PvP issue, this problem comes from how the game's combat system is designed, how damage is calculated, how resistance is calculated...etc. I don't see any way out for this unless the whole combat system is tweaked, which seems unlikely due to the fact that the game is already in final stage.
<BR>Anyway this is a pessimistic view of the whole situation, comments welcomed.(The PvP switch seems so much a minor issue now doesn't it?)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
